criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  meet 2006 Sapporo classification criteria of APS;

          -  diagnosis of primary APS, exclude other etiologies of thrombosis;

          -  with three aPL medium-to-high titer positivity, namely lupus anticoagulant, anti
             cardiolipin antibody, and anti-β2 glycoprotein antibody;

          -  with at least one extra-criteria manifestations of APS, including thrombocytopenia,
             hemolytic anemia, aPL nephropathy, valve heart disease and neurological
             manifestations.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  overlap with other connective tissue diseases, such as systemic lupus erythematosus;

          -  during pregnancy;

          -  can not follow-up.
